<div id="lang-en" class="lang-section">

  <section>
    <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p><strong>Carga Clara</strong> ("the App", "we") is a fleet fuel management application. The Carga Clara project owner is the data controller for personal data collected through the App.</p>
    <div class="box"><strong>Privacy contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacidad@cargaclara.mx">privacidad@cargaclara.mx</a></div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Full name, employee ID, and job role</li>
      <li>GPS location at the time of each fuel load</li>
      <li>Odometer photographs (live, time-stamped)</li>
      <li>Fuel receipt photographs (live, time-stamped)</li>
      <li>Fuel load records: liters, unit price, total amount, date and time</li>
      <li>Vehicle performance data: km/liter efficiency per trip</li>
      <li>Device information: device ID, operating system, app version</li>
      <li>Usage logs: login events and in-app actions</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Purpose of Processing</h2>
    <p><strong>Primary purposes (required for the service):</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Anti-fraud control: cross-validation of liters × price vs. declared total</li>
      <li>Fleet performance monitoring: km/liter efficiency alerts</li>
      <li>Statistical reporting for fleet administrators and management</li>
      <li>Internal audit and corporate governance compliance</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Secondary purposes (subject to consent):</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Promotional communications from companies related to fleet management, fuel, and vehicle services</li>
      <li>Aggregated statistical analysis to improve App functionality</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="box-warn">
      <strong>Future commercial use notice:</strong> We may use your data for commercial purposes in the future, including charging for App usage or activating paid features. Any such change will be notified at least <strong>30 calendar days</strong> in advance, giving you the opportunity to object before it takes effect.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Report Suggestions</h2>
    <p>We may invite you to submit feedback on reports and dashboards. Suggestions will be used solely to improve App functionality, will not be publicly attributed to you, and may be incorporated into future versions without additional compensation.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Legal Basis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contractual necessity:</strong> to provide the App's core functionality</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> anti-fraud controls and fleet monitoring</li>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> promotional communications (revocable at any time)</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> compliance with applicable Mexican law (LFPDPPP)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fleet administrators and designated personnel within your organization</li>
      <li>Third-party technology providers under confidentiality agreements</li>
      <li>Companies related to fuel and fleet services, for promotional purposes with your prior consent</li>
      <li>Government authorities when required by law or court order</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data to unrelated third parties.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fuel load records and photos:</strong> 5 years per Mexican fiscal regulations</li>
      <li><strong>Usage logs and device data:</strong> 2 years from last activity</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing preferences:</strong> until consent withdrawal or deletion request</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8. Your Rights (ARCO)</h2>
    <p>Under the LFPDPPP you have the right to Access, Rectification, Cancellation, and Opposition regarding your personal data.</p>
    <div class="box">
      Submit requests to <a href="mailto:privacidad@cargaclara.mx">privacidad@cargaclara.mx</a> including your full name, employee ID, the right you wish to exercise, and a copy of valid ID. We will respond within <strong>20 business days</strong>.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>9. Security</h2>
    <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures including encrypted transmission (TLS), role-based access controls, audit logs, and secure cloud storage. In the event of a security breach affecting your rights, we will notify you as required by applicable law.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>Material changes — especially those involving commercial data uses — will be notified at least <strong>30 calendar days</strong> before taking effect via email or in-app notification. Continued use after the effective date constitutes acceptance.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
    <p>This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the United Mexican States, specifically the LFPDPPP and guidelines issued by the INAI. Disputes shall be submitted to the competent courts of Mexico City or to the INAI as supervisory authority.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <div class="box">
      <strong>Carga Clara</strong><br>
      <a href="mailto:privacidad@cargaclara.mx">privacidad@cargaclara.mx</a>
    </div>
  </section>

